The paper discusses the use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) for sequence to sequence translation, which is a common topic in the machine learning subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) architectures, which are commonly used in the subfield of Deep Learning (cs.LG). The paper applies these techniques to motion capture (MOCAP) sequences, which is a common topic in the subfield of Computer Vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of semi-supervised learning, which is a common topic in the subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of encoder-decoder networks, which are commonly used in the subfield of Neural Networks (cs.NE).
